e of our\ntreatment of n as a free parameter. We find n=-(2.0-2.3)+-0.3, somewhat steeper\nthan derived from the earlier temperature function data, in agreement with the\nlocal slope of the galaxy fluctuation spectrum from the APM survey, and\nsignificantly steeper than the standard CDM prediction.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 5 Feb 1998 05:19:37 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 9 Apr 1998 04:56:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-10-30"}
